======================================================================
PART 4: CONTINUED FRACTION STRUCTURE
======================================================================

Morgan-Voyce polynomials satisfy B_m(x) = (2+x)B_{m-1}(x) - B_{m-2}(x)
with B_0 = 1, B_1 = 2+x.

This means B_m/B_{m-1} has the continued fraction expansion:
  B_m/B_{m-1} = (2+x) - 1/((2+x) - 1/((2+x) - ...))
which is a periodic CF with period 1!

Convergence of B_m(1)/B_{m-1}(1) = F_{2m+1}/F_{2m-1} → φ²:
  m= 1: B_m/B_0 = 2.0000000000, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 6.18e-01
  m= 2: B_m/B_1 = 2.5000000000, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 1.18e-01
  m= 3: B_m/B_2 = 2.6000000000, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 1.80e-02
  m= 4: B_m/B_3 = 2.6153846154, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 2.65e-03
  m= 5: B_m/B_4 = 2.6176470588, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 3.87e-04
  m= 6: B_m/B_5 = 2.6179775281, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 5.65e-05
  m= 7: B_m/B_6 = 2.6180257511, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 8.24e-06
  m= 8: B_m/B_7 = 2.6180327869, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 1.20e-06
  m= 9: B_m/B_8 = 2.6180338134, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 1.75e-07
  m=10: B_m/B_9 = 2.6180339632, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 2.56e-08
  m=11: B_m/B_10 = 2.6180339850, φ² = 2.6180339887, diff = 3.73e-09

Fixed point of x ↦ (2+1) - 1/x = 3 - 1/x: x = (3+√5)/2 = φ² = 2.618034
Compare: fixed point of x ↦ 1 + 1/x: x = (1+√5)/2 = φ = 1.618034

