======================================================================
PART 7: CHEBYSHEV POLYNOMIALS AND THE UNIFIED FRAMEWORK
======================================================================

Chebyshev U_m connection:
U_m(cos θ) = sin((m+1)θ) / sin θ
B_m(x) = U_m(1 + x/2)

  m=0: B_m(1) = 1, U_m(3/2) = 1, F_1 = 1, match = True
  m=1: B_m(1) = 2, U_m(3/2) = 3, F_3 = 2, match = False
  m=2: B_m(1) = 5, U_m(3/2) = 8, F_5 = 5, match = False
  m=3: B_m(1) = 13, U_m(3/2) = 21, F_7 = 13, match = False
  m=4: B_m(1) = 34, U_m(3/2) = 55, F_9 = 34, match = False
  m=5: B_m(1) = 89, U_m(3/2) = 144, F_11 = 89, match = False
  m=6: B_m(1) = 233, U_m(3/2) = 377, F_13 = 233, match = False
  m=7: B_m(1) = 610, U_m(3/2) = 987, F_15 = 610, match = False

THE UNIFIED VIEW:

1. Interval Q_k = |D_m(2πk/p)|² = Dirichlet kernel squared
2. prod(1+Q_k) = B_m(1) = U_m(3/2) = F_p
3. U_m(3/2) = value of Chebyshev polynomial at x = 3/2 = cos(iθ)
   where θ = arccosh(3/2) ≈ 0.9624
   cosh(0.9624) = 1.499974

