======================================================================
PART 10: TRANSFER MATRIX TRACE FORMULA FOR H
======================================================================

Rook placement interpretation:
H = #{σ ∈ S_p : σ(i+1) - σ(i) mod p ∈ S for all i}

For S = {1,...,m} (Interval):
  Each step goes forward by 1 to m positions (mod p)
  This is like a PAWN moving on a circular chessboard!

Bipartite matching formulation:
  H = perm(M) where M is a (p-1)×p matrix
  M[i,v] = 1 iff vertex v can be visited at step i
  This permanent counts Hamiltonian paths.

