PART 11: THE LATTICE GAS BRIDGE — OCF MEETS FIBONACCI
======================================================================

Fibonacci = independent set polynomial of path graph:
  F_n = I(P_{n-2}, 1)

OCF = independent set polynomial of odd-cycle graph:
  H(T) = I(Ω(T), 2)

For the Interval tournament:
  F_p = prod(1+Q_k) = independent set poly of ??? at activity ???

Verify: F_n = I(P_{n-2}, 1):
Standard result: number of independent sets of P_n (n vertices) = F_{n+2}
  P_1 (1 vertices): F_3 = 2
  P_2 (2 vertices): F_4 = 3
  P_3 (3 vertices): F_5 = 5
  P_4 (4 vertices): F_6 = 8
